e separation of shrines and temples. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} [[1869]] {{ill|May 9|ja|5月9日|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Emperor Meiji|ja|明治天皇|12=draft}} entered Edo Castle from Kyoto, marking the foundation of Tokyo as the new capital.
