{{Not to be confused with|March 28|qq=March 28}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月廿八|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 28일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 28''' is the 28th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Enryaku|Enryaku]] 23rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[804]] [[:en:May 11|May 11]]) – 【Saichō】 (最澄) and 【Kūkai】 (空海) entered Tang China as [[:en:Japanese missions to Tang China|Kentōshi (envoy to Tang China)]]. * [[Enbun]] 1st year/[[:en:Zhengping|Shōhei]] 11th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1356]] [[:en:April 29|April 29]]) – The Northern Court changed its era name from [[:en:Bun'ei|Bunna]] to [[:en:Enbun|Enbun]]. * [[Keichō]] 16th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1611]] [[:en:May 10|May 10]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Ieyasu|Tokugawa Ieyasu]] ascended to Kyoto, calling upon [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyori|Toyotomi Hideyori]] at [[:en:Nijō Castle|Nijō Castle]] for a meeting, signifying a reversal in the relationship between the Tokugawa and Toyotomi clans. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[:en:April 20|April 20]]) – The {{ill|Shinbutsu Bunri†Shinbutsu_Bunri|ja|神仏判然令|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinbutsu Bunri†Shinbutsu_Bunri|qq=}} was promulgated, prohibiting the syncretism of Shinto and Buddhism and mandating the separation of shrines and temples. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1869]] [[:en:May 9|May 9]]) – [[:en:Emperor Meiji|Emperor Meiji]] entered Edo Castle from Kyoto, marking the foundation of Tokyo as the new capital.
== Births == * [[:en:Enpō|Enpō]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1676]] [[:en:May 10|May 10]]) – {{ill|Fushimi-no-miya Kuninaga Shinnō|ja|伏見宮邦永親王|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fushimi-no-miya Kuninaga Shinnō|qq=}}, the 14th head of the Fushimi-no-miya (died [[1726]]). == Deaths == * [[Tenna]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1682]] [[:en:May 5|May 5]]) – [[:en:Nishiyama Sōin|Nishiyama Sōin]], a renga master (born [[1605]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[:en:May 17|May 17]]) – [[:en:Mōri Takachika|Mōri Takachika]], the head of the Chōshū Domain (born [[1819]]).
