== Events == * [[:en:Enryaku|Enryaku]] 23rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[804]] [[:en:May 11|May 11]]) – 【Saichō】 (最澄) and 【Kūkai】 (空海) entered Tang China as [[:en:Japanese missions to Tang China|Kentōshi (envoy to Tang China)]]. * [[Enbun]] 1st year/[[:en:Zhengping|Shōhei]] 11th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1356|1356]] [[:en:April 29|April 29]]) – The Northern Court changed its era name from [[:en:Bun'ei|Bunna]] to [[:en:Enbun|Enbun]]. * [[Keichō]] 16th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1611|1611]] [[:en:May 10|May 10]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Ieyasu|Tokugawa Ieyasu]] ascended to Kyoto, calling upon [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyori|Toyotomi Hideyori]] at [[:en:Nijō Castle|Nijō Castle]] for a meeting, signifying a reversal in the relationship between the Tokugawa and Toyotomi clans. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[:en:April 20|April 20]]) – The {{ill|Shinbutsu Bunri†Shinbutsu_Bunri|ja|神仏判然令|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinbutsu Bunri†Shinbutsu_Bunri|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 神仏分離}} was promulgated, prohibiting the syncretism of Shinto and Buddhism and mandating the separation of shrines and temples. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1869]] [[:en:May 9|May 9]]) – [[:en:Emperor Meiji|Emperor Meiji]] entered Edo Castle from Kyoto, marking the foundation of Tokyo as the new capital.
== Births == * [[:en:Enpō|Enpō]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1676|1676]] [[:en:May 10|May 10]]) – {{ill|Fushimi-no-miya Kuninaga Shinnō|ja|伏見宮邦永親王|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fushimi-no-miya Kuninaga Shinnō|qq=}}, the 14th head of the Fushimi-no-miya (died [[:en:1726|1726]]). == Deaths == * [[Tenna]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1682|1682]] [[:en:May 5|May 5]]) – [[:en:Nishiyama Sōin|Nishiyama Sōin]], a renga master (born [[:en:1605|1605]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[:en:May 17|May 17]]) – [[:en:Mōri Takachika|Mōri Takachika]], the head of the Chōshū Domain (born [[1819]]).
